source: crates/carta/tests/golden_e2e.rs
expression: output
---
<div id="lists" class="cell markdown">
<p>A bullet list opens right after a paragraph line, with no blank
between:</p>
<ul>
<li>apples</li>
<li>pears</li>
</ul>
<p>An ordered list interrupts the same way:</p>
<ol>
<li>second</li>
<li>third</li>
</ol>
<p>A parenthesized or roman marker has a list shape but no enabled style
here, so it breaks off as its own plain paragraph rather than folding
in:</p>
<p>(5) parenthesized</p>
<p>A decimal marker closed by a single paren stays prose and folds in,
so these two lines remain one paragraph: 1) not a list 2) still
prose</p>
</div>
